metadata.name: Zometric #157
metadata.description:
A journey into geometric shapes.
Real art is not hidden behind complicated and obscure forms. In this collection, we have tried to achieve a unique visual clarity by using the basic visual elements. A pure mixture between piet mondrian and paul klee. A combination of visual language of classical and modern art movements. Over 15 000 combination can be generated.
Made in p5.js

metadata.name: Fx(poritz) #50
metadata.description:
Fx(poritz) is a generative NFT collection of mysterious and magical creatures. This is a continuation of my previous work published on Hic et Nunc/Teia.

It was build with layered PNGs, using Photoshop and the Paint3D software. There are 5 features, and every iteration generates an unique poritz to call yours. There is 5% of chance to generate a RGB poritz, and 3% to mint a Trippy one.

metadata.name: E-Klipse 21 #5
metadata.description:
Satoshi Nakamoto, the architect of Bitcoin, is the artist who left the most profound impact on the future of Humanity. Due to his invention, We are not only creating or collecting art on the blockchains but also acquiring new freedoms.
The code was simple and worked. This piece attempts to symbolize the simplicity of Bitcoin's design.

metadata.name: Phantoms #43
metadata.description:
Phantoms is a series of hazy memories of distant places. Some tranquil, others sinister, each scene is as much defined by what is revealed as by what remains unseen.

In this collection I aim to juxtapose hard and soft. Blocky shapes form the core of the compositions. Upon these surfaces, soft textures appear to flow and drip over the sides. Varying levels of opacity, lighting, and fog effects further soften the scenes to create an atmospheric, dream-like quality. By remaining semi-abstract, each of the color palettes are given the space to influence the mood dramatically.

metadata.name: contrapuntos #421
metadata.description:
Musical counterpoint is to me an abstraction of the layered, intertwining rhythms of every activity we carry on in our lives. With a global tempo typically set in days, we fit all sorts of temporal structures where our joys and fears live and play out over the span of our lives. This series is a metaphorical transposition of the musical counterpoint into a visual space, sometimes with repeating patterns, sometimes with broken structures, sometimes isolated notes / hours / souls.

Artwork by Marcelo Soria-RodrÃ­guez, @msoriaro. Made with p5js & glsl.
